com.teamviewer.sdk.screensharing.api

Enum TVCreationError

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<TVCreationError>
      • com.teamviewer.sdk.screensharing.api.TVCreationError
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<TVCreationError>

    public enum TVCreationError
extends Enum<TVCreationError>
    Enumeration of errors, which can happen during session creation. Used as parameter with TVSessionCreationCallback.onTVSessionCreationFailed(TVCreationError).

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      DEVICE_OS_NOT_SUPPORTED
      The Android version of the device is lower than Android 4.0 (API Level 14).
      INTERNAL_ERROR
      An unexpected internal error occurred.
      NO_NETWORK_CONNECTION
      A network connection could no be established.
      SESSION_ALREADY_RUNNING
      There is already a session running or in the process of being created.
      TOKEN_INVALID
      The supplied SDK Token was not accepted by the TeamViewer server, because it is invalid.
      USER_CANCELLED
      The user cancelled the creation of a new session.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • INTERNAL_ERROR

        public static final TVCreationError INTERNAL_ERROR
        An unexpected internal error occurred. One reason for this error can be an incorrect packaging of the .so libraries coming with the SDK into the app.

      • DEVICE_OS_NOT_SUPPORTED

        public static final TVCreationError DEVICE_OS_NOT_SUPPORTED
        The Android version of the device is lower than Android 4.0 (API Level 14).

      • SESSION_ALREADY_RUNNING

        public static final TVCreationError SESSION_ALREADY_RUNNING
        There is already a session running or in the process of being created.

      • NO_NETWORK_CONNECTION

        public static final TVCreationError NO_NETWORK_CONNECTION
        A network connection could no be established. Either the network is disabled or the connection is not good enough for connecting to the TeamViewer servers.

      • TOKEN_INVALID

        public static final TVCreationError TOKEN_INVALID
        The supplied SDK Token was not accepted by the TeamViewer server, because it is invalid. Note that network errors preventing the check could also cause this error.

      • USER_CANCELLED

        public static final TVCreationError USER_CANCELLED
        The user cancelled the creation of a new session.
